The paper deals with coded caching, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The use of line graphs of bipartite graphs and projective geometries over finite fields suggests a connection to graph theory and algebraic coding theory (cs.DS). The problem of reducing peak traffic in broadcast networks is a networking problem (cs.NI). The use of coded transmissions and caching suggests a connection to distributed systems (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with the subpacketization of coded caching schemes, which is a problem in complexity theory (cs.CC).
